com.quantcomponents.algo
Interface ITradingHierarchyManager

All Known Subinterfaces:
IStockDatabaseTradingManager, ITradingManager
public interface ITradingHierarchyManager

Manager of the algorithm hierarchy. The algorithm hierarchy is composed by four levels:

  • An ITradingAgentFactory, that corresponds to an algorithm family, accessed by means of TradingAgentFactoryHandle
  • Several TradingAgentConfiguration, corresponding to the specific algorithm, created by applying a specific configuration to an algorith family, accessed by means of TradingAgentConfigurationHandle
  • Several TradingAgentBinding, that connect a specific algorithm to a set of inputs, accessed by means of TradingAgentBindingHandle
  • A set of ITradingAgentExecution, corresponding to specific runs of the algorithm bound to a set of inputs, accessed by means of TradingAgentExecutionHandle
All the mentioned types are opaque, and they are not meant to be used directly. This service lets callers browse the entity hierarchy without direct access, through the use of handles. Creation, removal and use of the entities is done through other interfaces:

See Also:
IHierarchyItemHandle, ITradingFactoryManager, ITradingAgentConfigurationManager, ITradingAgentBindingManager, ITradingAgentExecutionManager
